Steps:¶

  1. Did the basic data statistics about and data processing like replacing missing values. For replacing missing values Iused model based imputation using linear regression(LR).
  2. Gone through some data analysis and written my observations inline after the plots.
  3. Took the Key performance indicator(KPI) as RMSE.
  4. Tried to minimize it using various models with hyperparameter tuning using GridSearch and RandomSearch. Found XGBoost Regressor to be giving the least RMSE.
  5. plotted the feature importance for tree based models and found Absolute Temperature(AT) and Temperature(T) as most important features.
  6. Compared the models as shown in the table above.
